Ethan Allen Interiors Inc

Rai Favela |
Viernes, Julio 21, 2017







Four analysts have issued estimates for Ethan Allen Interiors' earnings, with the highest EPS estimate coming in at $0.51 and the lowest estimate coming in at $0.41.Among 5 analysts covering Ethan Allen (NYSE:ETH), 3 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 2 Hold. Raymond James downgraded the shares of ETH in report on Wednesday, October 28 to "Outperform" rating. Ls Limited Liability Corp has invested 0% in Ethan Allen Interiors Inc. KeyCorp analyst B. Thomas now forecasts that the company will earn $1.45 per share for the year, down from their prior estimate of $1.56.
Zacks presents analysts with an ABR (Average Broker Rating), based on the sell-side recommendations. Bowling Port Mngmt Lc owns 0.09% invested in Ethan Allen Interiors Inc. The company reported $0.23 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, missing the Thomson Reuters' consensus estimate of $0.27 by $0.04. The business had revenue of $180.20 million during the quarter, compared to analysts' expectations of $184.18 million. Ethan Allen Interiors had a return on equity of 11.31% and a net margin of 5.33%.The company said sales in the final quarter of the year were hurt by an especially weak month of April, and tough comparative numbers from the previous year. The Netols Asset Management Inc holds 219,549 shares with $8.09M value, down from 228,956 last quarter. ETH was included in 11 notes of analysts from July 29, 2015. It dived, as 16 investors sold Ethan Allen Interiors Inc. shares while 62 reduced holdings. Stifel Nicolaus decreased their target price on shares of Ethan Allen Interiors from $34.00 to $30.00 and set a "hold" rating on the stock in a report on Friday, April 28th. On Thursday, April 27 the stock rating was maintained by Telsey Advisory Group with "Outperform". Finally, BidaskClub downgraded Ethan Allen Interiors from a "buy" rating to a "hold" rating in a report on Saturday, July 8th. Six research analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating, one has issued a buy rating and one has assigned a strong buy rating to the company. Ethan Allen Interiors has a consensus rating of "Hold" and an average price target of $35.00.Several other hedge funds have also modified their holdings of the company. Finally, State Street Corp increased its stake in Ethan Allen Interiors by 6.8% in the first quarter. State of Alaska Department of Revenue now owns 4,900 shares of the company's stock worth $150,000 after buying an additional 2,140 shares in the last quarter.Karpas Strategies LLC continued to hold its position in Ethan Allen Interiors Inc. State of Alaska D